  "market_context": "Bitcoin trading on Coinbase 5-minute chart; price had formed a prior demand zone, then dipped slightly below a swing low before reversing upward with strong momentum.",
  "key_observation": "Price printed a lower low while MACD printed a higher low (bullish divergence), coinciding with a failure test of support at a key demand zone — three confluencing bullish signals.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst selected the standard MACD indicator in TradingView and modified its settings: fast length = 3, slow length = 10, signal smoothing = 16, both MAs set to SMA, colors changed to purple/black.",
    "Step 2: The analyst identified a prior swing low and noted that price briefly dipped below it (failure test), then reversed sharply upward.",
    "Step 3: The analyst observed that while price made a lower low, the MACD line formed a higher low — confirming bullish divergence.",
    "Step 4: The analyst confirmed the setup occurred within a pre-identified demand zone (key support area from left-side structure), adding third confluence.",
    "Step 5: Entry was placed at the close of the candle confirming the failure test; stop loss placed just below the low of that pattern; target set at 1:2 risk-to-reward."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade executed with 1:2 risk-to-reward; profit locked in after a relatively quick move up on 5m candles.",
  "lessons": "Confluence of failure test, bullish divergence, and demand zone significantly increases scalp probability; modified MACD (fast=3, slow=10, signal=16) enhances responsiveness for short-term entries.",
